Professional sports can take you on many of unexpected journeys and new places.  Although my time at the courage was short, I was able to meet some amazing people along the way. To the fans, wow you guys are some of the most supportive fans in the league.  You guys welcomed me to North Carolina with open arms and I am forever grateful for the endless support the past two years. So thank you for all of the love along the way. To my teammates, you guys made me feel right at home immediately. I had some of the best times with this team and moments that I will cherish forever.  I leave knowing I gained friends, but more importantly I leave knowing I gained family.  I now have some of the best friends and lifers. 

With that being said, I am so excited to be joining @racinglouisvillefc and getting the opportunity to continue my career with a club that is striving to be the absolute best in every aspect. The culture they have created is exactly what I want to be a part of, and I can't wait to get started. I'm looking forward to meeting the team and all of the Racing fans.  I want to bring an NWSL Championship to the city of Louisville, and I can't think of a better team and staff to do that with.  Let's do this💜

Global Accessibility Awareness Day (#GAAD) aims to promote awareness and dedication to inclusion, highlighting the importance of digital accessibility for people with disabilities worldwide.

Soccer player @carson.pickett recently spoke with #MAKERSWomen about advocating for Global #Accessibility Awareness Day (GAAD) and what she hopes to see specific achievements on its 20th anniversary.

“Instead of staring and wondering what may be different about someone, having the confidence to ask the questions and have those discussions would be really beneficial to spreading awareness. GAAD is important for me because I am a part of that community and it’s had a really big impact on my life. One specific achievement I hope to see is having more days or celebrating GAAD more than one month out of the year. We are all beautifully different and we should celebrate that.”

Visit the #linkinbio for Carson’s full MAKERS profile!

We are so excited to officially announce "Katie Lund and Carson Pickett's Kick Cancer Silent Auction" with you all.  We recently had the opportunity to visit @nortonchildrens and we both realized that we wanted to find a way to bring joy to the children at Nortons. So together we started a Kick Cancer fundraising campaign to raise money for new toys, games, activities and upgraded play spaces for the inpatient oncology unit at Norton Children's Hospital. We are so excited to make a difference in the lives of family's here in Louisville and we would love your support. 
-The link to the silent auction is here: https://e.givesmart.com/events/yak/ 
-You can also support by donating to our campaign at this link: https://p2p.onecause.com/kickcancer

We are so grateful for your support💜
